lead_paragraph: Boss, but Elected A discontented Tammany district leader has suggested to Christopher D. Sullivan that this would be a good time to resign as leader of the organization. Thereupon Mr. Sullivan reminds his critic that the latter represents only one-seventieth of the votes on the Tammany executive committee.
